        "C) No primary concept — all recipients are equal, and shipment-level decisions require all-party consent"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Option B — explicitly require a primary recipient designation at creation. This cleanly solves backward compatibility (partner APIs receive the primary) and provides a clear owner for shipment-level decisions."
    },
    {
      "type": "ambiguity",
      "description": "The pricing and billing model for multi-recipient shipments is unspecified. A shipment with 3 recipients going to 3 different addresses is fundamentally different from one recipient — it affects cost, invoicing, and refund logic.",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["Finance/billing", "End customers (senders)", "Product"],
